<br>
I have a few suggestions for improvement of the board, please take them as constructive criticism.  I am admin on a couple boards and have some ideas for improvement.<br>
<br>
1. Themes.  2 of the foums, Hibernian Alliance Council and Admin Roundtable have different Themes than all the other boards (different graphics/colors).  It would be nice to have them all the same.  This can be done in the admin controlls where you can configure one forum to look the way you want, then tell all the other forums to mimic that forum.<br>
<br>
2. Colums.  The main board has the moderator column turned on but no moderators assigned or displayed, this column could be turned off to clean up the page a little.  Different forums have different columns turned on.  All have new topic, topic, replies, last comment, and started by.  But a couple have views and rating, and only some forums alow posticons.  As with the Themes I would make the format uniform between them all for a more user friendly page.  Also as with themes you can configure one forum and tell the other ones to mimic its formatting.<br>
<br>
3. There are two topic where a guild directory is maintained, one in the Guilds forum and one in The War Room forum.  It's hard enough to get guilds to read the boards let alone post their info on the directory, it would be a lot easier to have them all in one place.  First you have to decide if that information should be private or not.  Considering the info available on the Camelot Herald I would say it's pretty public.  I recommend having just one forum called &quot;Directory&quot; and having 2 sticky forums inside, one for Guilds and the other for Allainces.  Every guild/alliance gets one post on that forum with their info.  If it changes they can edit their post.  This makes a single nice directory listing.  In the current guilds forum a lot of people have posted inside the forum instead of under the proper topic itself.<br>
<br>
4. Reduce the number of forums.  Right now there are 12 forums, a number which could be reduced.  There are a lot of redundant forums, leading to some being widely used and others being rarely touched.  The new meta-alliance has 2 forums and I'm not sure what the difference is between them.  I have found it is better to have a single main forum where all discussion goes on then create additional forums as needed, if there is something popular that can be given its own forum.<br>
<br>
a. General.  The main, public, wide open forum where everyone can chat.  News, Votes, and Polls can all be done here.<br>
b. Complaints, Whines, Flames.  It is good to have a separate forum where people can really cut loose, but others can avoid if they don't want to listen to it all.<br>
c. Roleplay.  Although not used much, it is nice to give roleplayers their own place of discussion, keeping all topic here In-Character.<br>
d. Directory.  This simply has 2 sticky topics, 1 for guild list, 1 for alliance list.  All posts under these 2 topics only.<br>
e. Marketplace.  This is the place to sell, buy, trade, make requests of crafters, and for crafters to discuss their skills.<br>
f. War Room.  This is the only password protected forum on the site.  The password is only to be given out in game, only to guild leaders and senior RvR operators.  It will be up to guild leaders who in their guild will get the password.  Security is a good idea, but with the number of people we want to participate it must be accepted that security won't be perfect.<br>
g. Suggestions.  This is the forum regarding the message board itself.  People can give suggestions or report problems and admins can discuss issues.<br>
<br>
